Real-Time Waste Classification & Carbon Impact Monitoring

An AI-powered real-time waste classification system built for Hack For Green Bharat.

This project uses Deep Learning + FastAPI + Pathway streaming to classify waste images and monitor waste trends in real-time.

🚀 Live Demo

🔗 Backend API (Render):
https://hack-for-green-bharat-wx1i.onrender.com

🔗 API Documentation (Swagger):
https://hack-for-green-bharat-wx1i.onrender.com/docs

🎯 Problem Statement

Improper waste segregation leads to:

Increased landfill overflow

Higher carbon emissions

Environmental pollution

Poor recycling efficiency

There is a need for an intelligent, real-time system that:

Automatically classifies waste

Tracks waste generation trends

Enables carbon impact estimation

Supports sustainability decisions

🧠 Solution Overview

Green AI is a real-time intelligent waste monitoring system that:

Accepts waste image uploads

Uses a Deep Learning model (ResNet18) for classification

Logs predictions into a streaming pipeline

Uses Pathway for real-time aggregation

Displays live waste distribution statistics

(Optional) Estimates carbon impact

🏗️ System Architecture

Frontend (Vercel)
⬇
FastAPI Backend (Render)
⬇
AI Waste Classification Model (PyTorch – ResNet18)
⬇
Waste Log (CSV)
⬇
Pathway Real-Time Streaming Engine
⬇
Live Aggregated Dashboard Data

🛠️ Tech Stack
AI / ML

PyTorch

ResNet18 (Fine-tuned)

Custom Waste Dataset (6 Classes)

Backend

FastAPI

Uvicorn

Python

python-multipart

Real-Time Processing

Pathway (Streaming & Aggregation Engine)

Frontend

HTML / JavaScript (Deployed on Vercel)

Deployment

Render (Backend + Pathway Worker)

Vercel (Frontend)

♻️ Waste Categories

The model classifies waste into:

Organic

Recyclable

Hazardous

Plastic

Metal

Glass

🔁 Real-Time Streaming Flow

User uploads image

Backend predicts waste type

Prediction appended to waste_log.csv

Pathway continuously monitors file

Real-time aggregation updates counts

Dashboard reflects updated statistics

📦 Installation (Local Development)
1️⃣ Clone Repository
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/green-ai.git
cd green-ai
2️⃣ Create Virtual Environment
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate   # Linux/Mac
venv\Scripts\activate      # Windows
3️⃣ Install Dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
4️⃣ Run Backend
uvicorn backend.app:app --reload

Open:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs

5️⃣ Run Pathway Streaming
python pathway_pipeline/stream.py
🌍 Deployment
Backend + Pathway

Deployed on Render (Linux environment)

Start Command:

uvicorn backend.app:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 10000

Background Worker:

python pathway_pipeline/stream.py
Frontend

Deployed on Vercel

